schemas.name: DeepLearningParametersV3

fields.name: checkpoint
fields.help: Model checkpoint to resume training with
fields.label: checkpoint

fields.name: override_with_best_model
fields.help: If enabled, override the final model with the best model found during training
fields.label: override_with_best_model

fields.name: use_all_factor_levels
fields.help: Use all factor levels of categorical variables. Otherwise, the first factor level is omitted (without loss of accuracy). Useful for variable importances and auto-enabled for autoencoder.
fields.label: use_all_factor_levels

fields.name: epochs
fields.help: How many times the dataset should be iterated (streamed), can be fractional
fields.label: epochs

fields.name: train_samples_per_iteration
fields.help: Number of training samples (globally) per MapReduce iteration. Special values are 0: one epoch, -1: all available data (e.g., replicated training data), -2: automatic
fields.label: train_samples_per_iteration

fields.name: target_ratio_comm_to_comp
fields.help: Target ratio of communication overhead to computation. Only for multi-node operation and train_samples_per_iteration=-2 (auto-tuning)
fields.label: target_ratio_comm_to_comp

fields.name: seed
fields.help: Seed for random numbers (affects sampling) - Note: only reproducible when running single threaded
fields.label: seed

fields.name: rho
fields.help: Adaptive learning rate time decay factor (similarity to prior updates)
fields.label: rho

fields.name: epsilon
fields.help: Adaptive learning rate smoothing factor (to avoid divisions by zero and allow progress)
fields.label: epsilon

fields.name: rate
fields.help: Learning rate (higher => less stable, lower => slower convergence)
fields.label: rate

fields.name: rate_annealing
fields.help: Learning rate annealing: rate / (1 + rate_annealing * samples)
fields.label: rate_annealing

fields.name: rate_decay
fields.help: Learning rate decay factor between layers (N-th layer: rate*alpha^(N-1))
fields.label: rate_decay

fields.name: momentum_start
fields.help: Initial momentum at the beginning of training (try 0.5)
fields.label: momentum_start

fields.name: momentum_ramp
fields.help: Number of training samples for which momentum increases
fields.label: momentum_ramp

fields.name: momentum_stable
fields.help: Final momentum after the ramp is over (try 0.99)
fields.label: momentum_stable

fields.name: input_dropout_ratio
fields.help: Input layer dropout ratio (can improve generalization, try 0.1 or 0.2)
fields.label: input_dropout_ratio

fields.name: hidden_dropout_ratios
fields.help: Hidden layer dropout ratios (can improve generalization), specify one value per hidden layer, defaults to 0.5
fields.label: hidden_dropout_ratios

fields.name: l1
fields.help: L1 regularization (can add stability and improve generalization, causes many weights to become 0)
fields.label: l1

fields.name: l2
fields.help: L2 regularization (can add stability and improve generalization, causes many weights to be small
fields.label: l2

fields.name: max_w2
fields.help: Constraint for squared sum of incoming weights per unit (e.g. for Rectifier)
fields.label: max_w2

fields.name: score_interval
fields.help: Shortest time interval (in secs) between model scoring
fields.label: score_interval

fields.name: score_training_samples
fields.help: Number of training set samples for scoring (0 for all)
fields.label: score_training_samples

fields.name: score_validation_samples
fields.help: Number of validation set samples for scoring (0 for all)
fields.label: score_validation_samples

fields.name: score_duty_cycle
fields.help: Maximum duty cycle fraction for scoring (lower: more training, higher: more scoring).
fields.label: score_duty_cycle

fields.name: classification_stop
fields.help: Stopping criterion for classification error fraction on training data (-1 to disable)
fields.label: classification_stop

fields.name: regression_stop
fields.help: Stopping criterion for regression error (MSE) on training data (-1 to disable)
fields.label: regression_stop

fields.name: quiet_mode
fields.help: Enable quiet mode for less output to standard output
fields.label: quiet_mode

fields.name: score_validation_sampling
fields.help: Method used to sample validation dataset for scoring
fields.label: score_validation_sampling

fields.name: variable_importances
fields.help: Compute variable importances for input features (Gedeon method) - can be slow for large networks
fields.label: variable_importances

fields.name: fast_mode
fields.help: Enable fast mode (minor approximation in back-propagation)
fields.label: fast_mode

fields.name: ignore_const_cols
fields.help: Ignore constant training columns (no information can be gained anyway)
fields.label: ignore_const_cols

fields.name: force_load_balance
fields.help: Force extra load balancing to increase training speed for small datasets (to keep all cores busy)
fields.label: force_load_balance

fields.name: replicate_training_data
fields.help: Replicate the entire training dataset onto every node for faster training on small datasets
fields.label: replicate_training_data

fields.name: single_node_mode
fields.help: Run on a single node for fine-tuning of model parameters
fields.label: single_node_mode

fields.name: shuffle_training_data
fields.help: Enable shuffling of training data (recommended if training data is replicated and train_samples_per_iteration is close to #nodes x #rows)
fields.label: shuffle_training_data

fields.name: missing_values_handling
fields.help: Handling of missing values. Either Skip or MeanImputation.
fields.label: missing_values_handling

fields.name: col_major
fields.help: Use a column major weight matrix for input layer. Can speed up forward propagation, but might slow down backpropagation (Experimental).
fields.label: col_major

fields.name: max_categorical_features
fields.help: Max. number of categorical features, enforced via hashing (Experimental)
fields.label: max_categorical_features

fields.name: reproducible
fields.help: Force reproducibility on small data (will be slow - only uses 1 thread)
fields.label: reproducible

fields.name: export_weights_and_biases
fields.help: Whether to export Neural Network weights and biases to H2O Frames
fields.label: export_weights_and_biases

fields.name: balance_classes
fields.help: Balance training data class counts via over/under-sampling (for imbalanced data).
fields.label: balance_classes

fields.name: class_sampling_factors
fields.help: Desired over/under-sampling ratios per class (in lexicographic order). If not specified, sampling factors will be automatically computed to obtain class balance during training. Requires balance_classes.
fields.label: class_sampling_factors

fields.name: max_after_balance_size
fields.help: Maximum relative size of the training data after balancing class counts (can be less than 1.0). Requires balance_classes.
fields.label: max_after_balance_size

fields.name: max_confusion_matrix_size
fields.help: Maximum size (# classes) for confusion matrices to be printed in the Logs
fields.label: max_confusion_matrix_size

fields.name: max_hit_ratio_k
fields.help: Max. number (top K) of predictions to use for hit ratio computation (for multi-class only, 0 to disable)
fields.label: max_hit_ratio_k

fields.name: model_id
fields.help: Destination id for this model; auto-generated if not specified
fields.label: model_id

fields.name: drop_na20_cols
fields.help: Drop columns with more than 20% missing values
fields.label: drop_na20_cols

fields.name: score_each_iteration
fields.help: Whether to score during each iteration of model training
fields.label: score_each_iteration

fields.name: __meta
fields.help: Metadata on this schema instance, to make it self-describing.
fields.label: __meta

schemas.name: GLMParametersV3

fields.name: family
fields.help: Family. Use binomial for classification with logistic regression, others are for regression problems.
fields.label: family

fields.name: solver
fields.help: Auto will pick solver better suited for the given dataset, in case of lambda search solvers may be changed during computation. IRLSM is fast on on problems with small number of predictors and for lambda-search with L1 penalty, L_BFGS scales better for datasets with many columns.
fields.label: solver

fields.name: alpha
fields.help: distribution of regularization between L1 and L2.
fields.label: alpha

fields.name: lambda_search
fields.help: use lambda search starting at lambda max, given lambda is then interpreted as lambda min
fields.label: lambda_search

fields.name: nlambdas
fields.help: number of lambdas to be used in a search
fields.label: nlambdas

fields.name: standardize
fields.help: Standardize numeric columns to have zero mean and unit variance
fields.label: standardize

fields.name: beta_epsilon
fields.help: beta esilon -> consider being converged if L1 norm of the current beta change is below this threshold
fields.label: beta_epsilon

fields.name: prior
fields.help: prior probability for y==1. To be used only for logistic regression iff the data has been sampled and the mean of response does not reflect reality.
fields.label: prior

fields.name: lambda_min_ratio
fields.help: min lambda used in lambda search, specified as a ratio of lambda_max
fields.label: lambda_min_ratio

fields.name: use_all_factor_levels
fields.help: By default, first factor level is skipped from the possible set of predictors. Set this flag if you want use all of the levels. Needs sufficient regularization to solve!
fields.label: use_all_factor_levels

fields.name: max_active_predictors
fields.help: Maximum number of active predictors during computation. Use as a stopping criterium to prevent expensive model building with many predictors.
fields.label: max_active_predictors

fields.name: balance_classes
fields.help: Balance training data class counts via over/under-sampling (for imbalanced data).
fields.label: balance_classes

fields.name: class_sampling_factors
fields.help: Desired over/under-sampling ratios per class (in lexicographic order). If not specified, sampling factors will be automatically computed to obtain class balance during training. Requires balance_classes.
fields.label: class_sampling_factors

fields.name: max_after_balance_size
fields.help: Maximum relative size of the training data after balancing class counts (can be less than 1.0). Requires balance_classes.
fields.label: max_after_balance_size

fields.name: max_confusion_matrix_size
fields.help: Maximum size (# classes) for confusion matrices to be printed in the Logs
fields.label: max_confusion_matrix_size

fields.name: max_hit_ratio_k
fields.help: Max. number (top K) of predictions to use for hit ratio computation (for multi-class only, 0 to disable)
fields.label: max_hit_ratio_k

fields.name: model_id
fields.help: Destination id for this model; auto-generated if not specified
fields.label: model_id

fields.name: drop_na20_cols
fields.help: Drop columns with more than 20% missing values
fields.label: drop_na20_cols

fields.name: score_each_iteration
fields.help: Whether to score during each iteration of model training
fields.label: score_each_iteration

fields.name: __meta
fields.help: Metadata on this schema instance, to make it self-describing.
fields.label: __meta
